    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-05-04T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-05-04T13:00:00-05:00" n="501"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d501">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.512/3497: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Nogales</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Damm</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nogales</hi>, Ariz</placeName>., <date
                            calendar="gregorian" when="1929-05-04T12:00:00-06:00">May 4,
                            1929—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received May 5—6 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to my telegram of May 2nd<note n="73" xml:id="d501fn73">See undated
                        telegram, <ref target="#pg_412">p. 412</ref>.</note>
                    <hi rend="italic">en clair</hi> with regard to the payment of taxes to the
                    reestablished government by American citizens; the Federal internal revenue
                    inspector for this district has informed individual Americans that the Federal
                    Government objected to their applying to American consuls or the State
                    Department for relief of any kind in this connection. He pointed out that
                    article 27 of the Constitution forbade the application for such relief;
                    furthermore, if they did, a clause of this article provides for the closing of
                    the business pending a hearing before the district judge.</p>
                <p>Embassy informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Damm</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
